message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: Network Latency Measurements Under Load Generation Workloads on Two Nodes
abstract: This dataset documents a network latency measurement experiment using load
  generation workloads executed across two nodes. The methodology involved configuring
  and running a load generator script alongside a forwarding component, capturing
  latency metrics during operation while also recording energy consumption. Multiple
  configurations of packet rate and size were used to evaluate performance characteristics
  under varying conditions. Resulting data files containing the captured latencies
  are included for analysis.
